Etymology: The species is named after Dr. Darnas Dana ( 04.01.1947 – 27.08.2007 ), former Vice Rector of Planning and Development (
1999–2003
), Bogor Agricultural University, Indonesia , and Director of Fish Health and Environment, Directorate General of Aquaculture, Ministry of Marine Affairs and Fisheries (
2004–2006
), who invited the second author to carry out fish parasitological research at IPB .
